<br>
First, there is a <!--EZCODE LINK START--><a href="http://pub6.ezboard.com/fthemagicianstowerfrm29">Magician Pet Forum</a><!--EZCODE LINK END-->, where you will find many wonderful discussions about pets, for example <!--EZCODE LINK START--><a href="http://pub6.ezboard.com/fthemagicianstowerfrm29.showMessage?topicID=288.topic"> MAGICIAN PETS FREQUENTLY ASKED QUESTIONS (FAQ)</a><!--EZCODE LINK END-->.<br>
<br>
Second, here is the short answer.  In the hands of a pet, a weapon does a max of twice the weapon's printed damage. For example, an <!--EZCODE ITALIC START--><i> Axe of the Ironback</i><!--EZCODE ITALIC END--> says it does 16 damage, so in a pet's hands, it will do 32 max when it hits.  If your pet is doing less than 32 points of damage max, then the weapon will improve it.  Some weapons, like a <!--EZCODE ITALIC START--><i> Weighted Axe</i><!--EZCODE ITALIC END-->, sadly do not work.<br>
<br>
When the pet starts dual weilding (29ish?), then giving it two handed weapons becomes a bad idea.  Then the only thing that makes sense is giving it a weapon with a proc, like a <!--EZCODE ITALIC START--><i> Gnoll Hide Lariat</i><!--EZCODE ITALIC END-->, that procs a stun.  Very useful, and available in Bazaar for about 25 pp each.<br>
<br>
Check out the forum and the FAQ above if you have more questions about pets, and remember, there is a lot more than just this GENERAL forum.<br>
<br>
